<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1322,1185,1451]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Having studied the 
<typeStatus box="[497,599,1185,1211]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[642,819,1185,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bucki">
<emphasis box="[642,819,1185,1210]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Anthaxia bucki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:35275" box="[837,929,1185,1211]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:35275" name="Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">MNCN</collectionCode>
) and comparing it with the 
<typeStatus pageId="7" pageNumber="8">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[354,458,1225,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kafkai">
<emphasis box="[354,458,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">A. kafkai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode box="[475,564,1225,1251]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/hj12-2xm7" name="National Museum Prague" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">NMPC</collectionCode>
), I find them to be conspecific and consider 
<taxonomicName box="[1086,1190,1225,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kafkai">
<emphasis box="[1086,1190,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">A. kafkai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a new junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[611,715,1265,1290]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bucki">
<emphasis box="[611,715,1265,1290]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">A. bucki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Unfortunately 
<bibRefCitation author="Cobos" box="[918,1086,1265,1291]" pageId="7" pageNumber="10" refString="Cobos, A. (1956) Ensayo monografico sobre las Anthaxia Eschs. (Coleoptera, Buprestidae) de America. Primera parte: Subgeneros Cylindrophora Sol. y Paracuris Obenb. Archivos de Instituto de Aclimatacion (Almeria), 5, 103 - 165." type="journal article" year="1956">
Cobos (
<number box="[1017,1078,1265,1291]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1956.0">1956</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
in his description published an illustration of 
<taxonomicName box="[601,701,1305,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bucki">
<emphasis box="[601,701,1305,1330]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">A. bucki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<number box="[778,808,1305,1331]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="78.0">78</number>
) which strongly differs from the 
<typeStatus box="[1219,1321,1305,1331]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">holotype</typeStatus>
(illustrated specimen possesses posteriorly strongly enlarged elytra and nearly convex pronotum); having relied on the illustration, I described this species once more.
</paragraph>
